  "texts": [
    "Each amino acid is represented by a one-hot feature vector and embedded as an input representation for PhiGnet.",
    "The ESM-1b embedding captures the unique amino acid at each specific site along the sequence, enabling the stacked GCN layers to acquire higher-level features from either EVCs or RCs using distinct convolutional filters.",
    "PhiGnet adopts dual channels consisting of stacked GCNs.",
    "In one channel, a stack of GCNs gathers information from the sequence embedding using evolutionarily coupled residues as graph nodes.",
    "In the other channel, the graph layers learn information about functionally significant residues using RCs as nodes."
  ],
